display.text: What is the client’s HIV status from previous study HIV testing?
Please do pre-test counseling and draw blood from client for rapid test.
Script 1: I will now ask about your current relationship status.
Are you still in a relationship with the woman who enrolled in this study during pregnancy?
Script 2 : Now I will ask you questions about the number of children you would like to have.
At the time your wife/partner became pregnant, did you want her to become pregnant, did you want her to wait until later, or did you not want any (more) children at all?
Would you like to have more children?
Do you think that your wife/partner wants the same number of children that you want, or does she want more or fewer than you want?
Who has the most influence on decisions about the timing and number of children you will have?
display.hint: Review options with client and choose one.

display.text: Script 3: Now I would like to talk about your HIV test results.
What was the result of your most recent HIV test?
Have you ever enrolled or registered into a HIV comprehensive care clinic (CCC)?
Have you been prescribed ART to manage your HIV infection?
Are you currently taking the treatment you were prescribed?
Script 4: Thank you for your time in answering these questions.
Now we will do the post-test counseling for the HIV test.
display.hint: The interviewer will record the HIV test results and provide post-test counsel for client concerning the results.
